556	\subsection{Use in Serre finiteness}
557	
558	For a proper geometrically integral curve $C$ over $k$, a two-affine cover with affine intersection always exists. The bundle $S$ then feeds the Serre-finiteness chain:
559	\begin{enumerate}
560	  \item The Mayer--Vietoris LES applied to $S$ and $\mathcal O_C$ relates $H^0$ and $H^1$ of $C$, $U_1$, $U_2$, and $U_1 \cap U_2$.
561	  \item The cover hypothesis identifies the fourth corner with the whole curve.
562	  \item Affineness of the pieces collapses $H^{>0}$ on those pieces, reducing the LES to a three-term sequence.
563	  \item Finiteness of each $H^0$ piece then implies finiteness of $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$.
564	\end{enumerate}
565	Steps~1--2 are supplied by this section; Steps~3--4 are deferred to subsequent sections.
