27	\paragraph{Pull-back: hand-construction over a split named-deferred Mathlib gap.}
28	Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_Pic_pullback} below was closed in iter-109 by a hand-construction that bundles the two iso-witnesses of a (missing) $\mathrm{Functor.Monoidal}\,(\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f)$ instance into a $\mathrm{MonoidHom}$ on the skeleta directly, then lifts via $\mathrm{Units.map}$. The construction depends on the \emph{pair} of named-deferred Mathlib gaps recorded as Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj} (tensor-preservation iso, the $\mu$-iso) and Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_oneIso} (unit-preservation iso, the $\varepsilon$-iso) below. The two are siblings of a single Mathlib gap — once Mathlib lands $(\mathrm{SheafOfModules.pullback}\,f).\mathrm{Monoidal}$ the pair collapses simultaneously to $\mathrm{MonoidalCategoryStruct.tensorObj}$-comparison and $\mathrm{Monoidal.}\varepsilon\mathrm{Iso}$. The named-deferral route is per analogist option~(c) of \texttt{analogies/c1-route.md}; see also the Phase~C1 row of \texttt{STRATEGY.md}.
