60	\section{Pull-back functoriality}
61	
62	% NOTE: post-iter-109 — the Lean bodies of `Pic.pullback`, `Pic.pullback_id`, and `Pic.pullback_comp` are now CLOSED, gated only on the two named-deferred Mathlib gaps Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj} (tensor-preservation iso) and Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_oneIso} (unit-preservation iso). The hand-construction is analogist option~(c) of \texttt{analogies/c1-route.md}, with the named-deferral split across a pair (was a single oracle at refactor-iter-109; the unit-half was split off during prover-iter-109 because protected signatures cannot return tuples). `\leanok` on the statement blocks reflects that the declarations type-check and that the proof bodies are closed modulo the two oracle isos.
63	\begin{theorem}\leanok
64	[Pull-back of line bundles]
65	  \label{thm:Scheme_Pic_pullback}
66	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Pic.pullback}
67	  Let $f \colon X \to Y$ be a morphism of schemes. The categorical pull-back functor $\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f \colon Y.\mathrm{Modules} \to X.\mathrm{Modules}$ induces a group homomorphism
68	  \[
69	    f^* \colon \Pic(Y) \;\to\; \Pic(X)
70	  \]
71	  by passing to invertible objects of the skeleton.
72	\end{theorem}
73	
74	\begin{proof}
75	  \uses{thm:Scheme_Pic_commGroup, thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj, thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_oneIso}
76	  \leanok
77	  The conceptual definition is $f^* = \mathrm{Units.map}(\mathrm{Skeleton.monoidHom}(\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f))$, i.e.\ the units functor applied to the monoid homomorphism on skeleta induced by a monoidal functor (\texttt{Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.Skeleton:111}). However, calling $\mathrm{Skeleton.monoidHom}$ would require a $\mathrm{Functor.Monoidal}\,(\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f)$ instance, which Mathlib~\texttt{b80f227} does not register.
78	
79	  The Lean construction therefore proceeds by \emph{hand-bundling} the two iso-witnesses ($\mu$-iso = Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj}; $\varepsilon$-iso = Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_oneIso}) into the underlying $\mathrm{MonoidHom}\,(\mathrm{Skeleton}\,Y.\mathrm{Modules})\,(\mathrm{Skeleton}\,X.\mathrm{Modules})$ directly:
80	  \begin{itemize}
81	    \item the underlying function is $\mathrm{Functor.mapSkeleton}\,(\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f)$ (Mathlib's lift of an arbitrary functor to skeleta);
82	    \item $\mathrm{map\_one'}$ is discharged by Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_oneIso} (followed by the projection $\mathrm{congr\_toSkeleton\_of\_iso}$ of an iso to an equality of skeleton classes);
83	    \item $\mathrm{map\_mul'}$ is discharged by Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj} (followed by the same skeleton-of-iso projection).
84	  \end{itemize}
85	  The composite $\mathrm{Units.map}\,(\text{this MonoidHom})$ is then a group homomorphism $\Pic(Y) \to \Pic(X)$ as required. When a future Mathlib refresh lands $(\mathrm{SheafOfModules.pullback}\,f).\mathrm{Monoidal}$ the two oracle theorems collapse simultaneously into $\mathrm{MonoidalCategoryStruct.tensorObj}$-comparison and $\mathrm{Monoidal.}\varepsilon\mathrm{Iso}$, and the hand-construction may be replaced by the literal $\mathrm{Units.map} \circ \mathrm{Skeleton.monoidHom}$ form.
86	\end{proof}
87	
88	\paragraph{Functoriality.}
89	The contravariant functoriality $(\mathrm{id}_X)^* = \mathrm{id}_{\Pic(X)}$ and $(g \circ f)^* = f^* \circ g^*$ is recorded by the following two lemmas; their Lean bodies are closed in iter-109 using $\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullbackId}$ and $\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullbackComp}$ respectively, plus the skeleton-of-iso projection used in $\mathrm{Pic.pullback}$.
