99	  \uses{thm:Scheme_Pic_pullback}
100	  \leanok
101	  $\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,(\mathrm{id}_X)$ is naturally isomorphic to the identity functor on $X.\mathrm{Modules}$ via $\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullbackId}$ (existing Mathlib infrastructure); the induced monoid hom on skeleta then collapses to the identity via the skeleton-of-iso projection.
